S"The accompanying\rfinancial statements have been prepared in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America,\rwhich contemplates continuation of the Company as a going concern. For the year ended December 31, 2014, the Company incurred a\rnet loss of $8,116,603. At December 31, 2014, the Company has negative working capital of $4,750,656 and an accumulated deficit\rof $18,358,081. A significant amount of additional capital will be necessary to advance the marketability of the Company's products\rto the point at which the Company can sustain operations. These conditions, among others, raise substantial doubt about the Company's\rability to continue as a going concern. Management's plans are to continue to raise capital through equity and debt offerings,\rand to expand sales as rapidly as economically viable. The accompanying consolidated financial statements do not include any adjustments\rthat might result from the outcome of this uncertainty."
